{
  "stem": "5470.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But he-- but I heard afterwards, from the Red Cross, because I asked by the Red Cross later on, after liberation, what happened to several people, and one was Heinus Eidefeld.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he was in Theresienstadt for about a week, and then further transported back to-- or also to Auschwitz, and [? whatever ?] happened.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was together with a friend of his.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And his brother is still living here, off the train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He lives in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And that one died in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they both together went to Theresienstadt-- to Auschwitz after Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I had lost all trace of Heinus after Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But from [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Felix, ?] we got to know that he had the-- perhaps you've heard the, the death walk from Auschwitz after the Russians controlled the-- Poland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And that was the big march from all these prisoners through Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And he ended up in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "That's where he died.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was-- in the middle of the night, after 12 o'clock, then they went over to-- in the first instance, then to the bigger barracks.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if they were living in the smaller houses there, than they knocked them on the door that you had to prepare yourself for transport.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what I took care of was in-- always that-- I kept them as inhabitants of the camp for a further three days.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So instead of dropping their state of the registration for the coupons, I kept them on for a further three days so-- because it was said to us anyhow, that it took them three days from Holland to Auschwitz and that rations were given to them in the train.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So, so that was-- the food pile side, that was my business.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what they could carry.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
